# SMTP configuration for contact form. Copy this file to `.env.local`
# and fill in real values if you want emails sent for real.
#
# Simple explanation (no need to understand the acronym):
# - SMTP is just the service your email account uses to send mail.
# - You provide a server address, port, username and password so the form can
#   log in and relay messages on your behalf.
# - If you don't know what to put here, leave the values blank and the app will
#   create a temporary fake account and give you a link to preview any messages.
#   That's handy for development or if you simply don't need real email yet.
#
# A typical Gmail setup:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USER=youremail@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=your_app_password

SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=dhruvsaini137@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your_smtp_password_or_app_password

# Alternatively, you can use SendGrid (recommended if you don't want to use
# your personal Gmail password). Create an API key in SendGrid and paste it
# below. If `SENDGRID_API_KEY` is set, the app will send via SendGrid instead
# of SMTP.
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=SG.xxxxxxxx.yyyyyyyy
